summary: We Bought Game Of Thrones Monopoly
body:
We Bought Game Of Thrones Monopoly

Its amazing, though we have only played twice in the like 4 days since we’ve bought it.

But! The important part is this:

We have this radical house rule that I personally came up with and thoroughly enjoy.

So!!! Say you are sitting on a property and you own it. Someone else lands on said property while you are there. They request a duel. You, as owner of said land, can allow or deny it. If neither of you own the square, it has to be a mutual or whatever, or if you own the square you can force them to battle.

The duel is just roll to see who gets a higher number, I’ll probably look for different ways to make the dueling interesting as well. Maybe knife throwing.. But you put things up for grabs.

Ant and I, the one time we dueled (it doesnt happen often because we rarely stand on a square together) I challenged him. I said, “Ill give you my last 3 silver stags and my final property if I lose. If i win, I want one set of your properties.”

He agreed. By luck. I got a higher number. He turned over his light blue properties.

Some other stuff led to me winning that game, but I wouldnt have gotten there had it not been for that.

Its fun. I just figured for Game of Thrones it needed more… violence.

summary: [SPOILERS] Watching the series for the first time and I just finished season 3.
title: [SPOILERS] Watching the series for the first time and I just finished season 3.
body:
I can’t process pain anymore.

Catelyn Stark was my favorite character and the “red wedding” was as utterly shocking as it was horrifying to watch. Everything seemed so happy and peaceful right before it happened, then the rains of castamere started playing and I knew it was all doomed to end. Seeing Talisa getting stabbed and dying with her unborn child, or Catelyn begging for her sons life really broke me.

Well that’s all I wanted to say. I have a lot of probably further emotional trauma to get through before April.

(Plz don’t talk about post S3 spoilers here)



Source: http://bit.ly/2D1p6rZ
